	Overview</p>
<p>
	Manage design assurance for the design and development of medical device products.&nbsp; Manage and facilitate the application of risk management for all Candela and Syneron medical device products.</p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	Position Description:</p>
<p>
	Provide Quality support to facilitate the rapid resolution of product complaints and/or safety issues. Support Failure Investigation.<br />
	Review and update Clinical and Technical FMEA.<br />
	&sect;&nbsp; Conduct internal quality system and design service quality audits.</p>
<p>
	Review Design History Files and Technical Files for conformance to applicable requirements.<br />
	Support product development efforts using theNew Product Development process.<br />
	Provide design assurance for the design and development of medical device products.<br />
	Update and facilitate the application of risk management for all medical device products.<br />
	Review of validation plans, methods and protocols, test methods, statistical analysis methods, and specification derivation and assignment.<br />
	Review, establish and mitigate risks for risk management reporting.<br />
	Review new and modified product designs for quality characteristics, including manufacturability, serviceability, testability, reliability, biocompatibility, sterility and conformance to product requirements.<br />
	Ensure that product development projects and changes to existing products are conducted in compliance with the FDA Quality System Regulation and Medical Device Directives.<br />
	Ensure successful transfer of new products to manufacturing. Review production processes for quality of verification and validation methods.<br />
	Review and approve verification and validation test plans. Ensure verification results demonstrate compliance to medical device standards.<br />
	Mentor project teams on verification/validation statistical methods and design controls.<br />
	Assist in product risk assessment efforts within project teams and manage updates to existing product lines.<br />
	Manage risk management file through product development cycle.<br />
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	<br />
	Minimum Qualifications:</p>
<p>
	Related experience in design quality within the medical device or pharmaceutical industry with a minimum of 5 years in FDA/MDD regulated industry<br />
	Experience in medical device product development from concept to manufacturing transfer and post-commercialization success measurement.<br />
	Bachelors of Engineering, Biomedical, Science or technical degree preferred<br />
	&sect;&nbsp; Working knowledge of ISO13485, Medical Device Directive and QSR/cGMP requirements</p>
<p>
	&sect;&nbsp; Working knowledge of electrical and laser safety standards such as IEC60601-1 and its corollaries, ISO60825 and 21 CFR 1040</p>
<p>
	&sect;&nbsp; Working knowledge of software design control standards and guidances such as IEC62304, Guidance for General Principles of Software Validation, GAMP4</p>
<p>
	&sect;&nbsp; Proven track record with design quality methodologies such as Product Qualification/Validation, Risk Management, Statistical Methods, and Corrective/Preventive Action.</p>
<p>
	&sect;&nbsp; Working knowledge of risk management standard ISO 14971. Experience in risk evaluation techniques, such as FMEA, fault tree analysis or HACCP.</p>
<p>
	Skilled in test plan development and root cause failure analysis.<br />
	Skilled in statistical methods, including ANOVA, statistical process control, sampling plans, gauge R&amp;R, and design of experiments.<br />
	Familiar with reliability analysis and test methods and test method validation.<br />
	Strong written/verbal communication skills<br />
	Experience in developing policies and procedures<br />
	Demonstrated experience/results in Quality System tools and Problem-Solving.<br />
	Manufacturing engineering or manufacturing quality engineering experience a plus.</p>
