			<description><![CDATA[<p>The successful candidate is responsible for achieving annual sales objectives for the assigned territory through the development, maintenance, and enhancement of key customer relationships. These customers include oncologists, urologists, nurses, pharmacists, pharmacy and therapeutics groups, tumor boards, teaching institutions, hospitals and formulary committees.</p><p><br /><strong><u>Responsibilities</u></strong></p><p><br />&bull; Effectively communicate appropriate technical, therapeutic, disease state and product information to customers in order to successfully promote the appropriate on label use of approved products within the territory.<br />&bull; Utilize effective selling techniques and marketing strategies to create and expand demand for all promoted brands.<br />&bull; Demonstrate advanced business acumen and account management skills<br />&bull; Understand and navigates the product/process throughout large institutions.<br />&bull; Successfully manage/coordinate simultaneous complex selling situations from enrollment to certification.<br />&bull; Develop and coordinate physician advocates for promoted oncology/urology products.<br />&bull; Arrange and coordinate effective promotional programs.<br />&bull; Work as a resource for various oncology organizations, teaching institutions, physicians, oncology nurses, pharmacy directors, therapeutic groups, etc.<br />&bull; Communicate regularly with his/her Team, Regional Sales Manager, Sales Director, Peers, Internal/External Partners and Clients in order to optimize resources and exceed customer expectations.<br />&bull; Work in a cross-functional team with Apheresis Nurse Specialists, Market Access Teams and On Call<br />&bull; Comply with all OIG/FDA and Corporate Policy&rsquo;s and Procedures.<br />&bull; Complete expense reports and other required administrative reports.<br />&bull; Attend training programs, conventions, and symposia.<br />&bull; Ongoing territory analysis and business planning.<br />&bull; Effectively manage a territory to achieve sales targets and stay within all approved budgets.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p><ul><li>Bachelor&#39;s Degree or equivalent.</li><li>Minimum of 5 or more years of Biotech/Pharmaceutical sales experience; Medical Device experience selling to hospital accounts is also highly desirable</li><li>Medicare Part B drug experience is ideal.</li><li><strong>Minimum of 2 years selling in the Oncology therapeutic market</strong>.</li><li>Consistent track record of successfully achieved sales targets.</li><li>Ability to think, plan, and act strategically.</li><li>In depth product and territory knowledge within the Oncology therapeutic market.</li><li>Ability to travel overnight for territory coverage (if applicable) and/or for company meetings.</li></ul>]]></description>
